🔷 Concept 1 — split() (8 min)
split() chops a string into a list of pieces wherever it sees a space:
pythonline = "RRC_Setup RSRP=-85.0 STATUS=FAIL"

pieces = line.split()

print(pieces)
# Output: ['RRC_Setup', 'RSRP=-85.0', 'STATUS=FAIL']
Think of it like cutting a sentence into words. Each word becomes an item in a list.
Now you can grab specific pieces by their index (position number, starting from 0):
pythonprint(pieces[0])   # RRC_Setup
print(pieces[1])   # RSRP=-85.0
print(pieces[2])   # STATUS=FAIL

🔷 Concept 2 — split() with a separator (5 min)
What if you want just the number from RSRP=-85.0? Split again — but this time split on the = sign:
pythonchunk = "RSRP=-85.0"

parts = chunk.split("=")

print(parts)
# Output: ['RSRP', '-85.0']

print(parts[1])
# Output: -85.0
You're splitting on a specific character instead of a space. Same idea, different separator.
But notice parts[1] is still text — it's the string "-85.0", not the number -85.0. To do math on it, convert it:
pythonvalue = float(parts[1])
# Now it's a real number: -85.0
float() converts text to a decimal number. int() converts text to a whole number. You'll use float() constantly for RSRP, throughput, SNR values.

🔷 Concept 3 — Chaining it together (5 min)
You can chain two splits in one line — split on space to get the chunk, then split on = to get the value:
pythonline = "RRC_Setup RSRP=-85.0 STATUS=FAIL"

rsrp_value = float(line.split()[1].split("=")[1])

print(rsrp_value)
# Output: -85.0
Reading it left to right:

line.split() — chop by spaces → ['RRC_Setup', 'RSRP=-85.0', 'STATUS=FAIL']
[1] — grab index 1 → 'RSRP=-85.0'
.split("=") — chop by = → ['RSRP', '-85.0']
[1] — grab index 1 → '-85.0'
float(...) — convert to number → -85.0


🔷 Your hands-on task (10 min)
Paste and run this on online-python.com — every line explained in the comments:
python# Simulated TM500-style log lines
log_lines = [
    "RRC_Setup RSRP=-85.0 STATUS=PASS",
    "Handover RSRP=-103.5 STATUS=FAIL",
    "NAS_Attach RSRP=-78.2 STATUS=PASS",
    "PDCP_Reorder RSRP=-91.0 STATUS=FAIL",
    "RRC_Reconfig RSRP=-88.5 STATUS=PASS"
]

# Store extracted values here
rsrp_values = []

for line in log_lines:
    # Step 1 — split line by spaces into pieces
    pieces = line.split()

    # Step 2 — grab the test name (index 0)
    test_name = pieces[0]

    # Step 3 — grab RSRP chunk (index 1), split by = , grab value, convert to float
    rsrp = float(pieces[1].split("=")[1])

    # Step 4 — grab STATUS chunk (index 2), split by =, grab value
    status = pieces[2].split("=")[1]

    # Step 5 — add rsrp to our list for later
    rsrp_values.append(rsrp)

    # Step 6 — print extracted values cleanly
    print(f"{test_name}: RSRP={rsrp} dBm -- {status}")

# After loop — calculate stats from extracted values
print(f"\n=== RSRP STATS ===")
print(f"Best RSRP  : {max(rsrp_values)} dBm")
print(f"Worst RSRP : {min(rsrp_values)} dBm")
print(f"Average    : {sum(rsrp_values) / len(rsrp_values):.1f} dBm")

Expected output:
