🔷 Two new things to notice:
rsrp_values.append(rsrp) — .append() adds an item to the end of a list. You're collecting all RSRP numbers as you loop so you can do stats after.
max(), min(), sum(), len() — Python built-in functions:

max() — biggest number in the list
min() — smallest number in the list
sum() — adds all numbers together
len() — counts how many items in the list
